課程教材 Course Material
	    This course will introduce advanced parametric design topics and develop the students’
ability to effectively use parametric design tools and interactive systems to create functional
prototypes of performative building components.

Computer + fabrication facilities are available to students during class times but it is highly
recommended that student also install the following software on their own laptops to work on
assignment at home. Additionally, basic Arduino microcontrollers and various sensor/actuator
components will be provided to the students in the second part of the semester for prototyping.
1. Rhinoceros 3D – nurbs surface modeling
(purchase required McNeel < http://www.rhino3d.com/sales/asia/Taiwan>)
2. Grasshopper – parametric modeling
(free download Grasshopper <http://www.grasshopper3d.com/page/download-1>)
3. Arduino IDE – microcontroller driver and software
(free download Arduino <http://arduino.cc/en/Main/Software>)    

參考書目 References
	    Asterios Agkathidis | Gabi Schillig. Performative Geometries. Amsterdam, Netherlands: BIS
Publishers, 2010.
Michael Hensel. Performance Oriented Architecture: Rethinking Architectural Design and
the Built Environment. Chichester, United Kingdom: Wiley 2013.
